## Post-Hoc Contrasts vs. Young Adults

<div class="two-col">
<div class="col">

| Group | $d_{t_0}$ | $d_{\lambda}$ | $d_{\kappa}$ |
|---|---|---|---|
| Young children (<7 y) | 1.47 | 1.65 | −0.83 |
| Children (7–12 y) | 0.96 | 1.26 | −0.19 |
| Adolescents (13–17 y) | −0.40 | 1.43 | 1.24 |
| **Older adults (65+ y)** | **−1.38** | **−1.16** | **0.14** |

Children: **large effects across all three parameters**

Older adults: **largest effect in $t_0$**, moderate $\lambda$, smaller $\kappa$

</div>
<div class="col">

![](figures/posthoc_heatmap.png)

</div>
